    "body": "Problem:  Edge cases to the delayed 'signcolumn' validation added\r\n          in #26406 may result in an incorrectly sized \"auto\" sign column.\r\nSolution: Store the number of added/deleted signs on a row to compare\r\n          to when counting to validate the range.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I [assumed](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26406#discussion_r1419077076) there were problems with this approach but hadn't found a failing test case until now.\r\n\r\nNot the biggest fan of the added complexity here but now at least now it is correct, and there is added test coverage.\n\r\n(The alternative of immediately validating as soon as signs are added/removed might be simpler but I'm too invested in trying to make this work now... Still seems more performant to me. This also works out better in the sense that we have the window context for the configured maximum at the point of validation.)",
            "created_at": "2024-01-05T13:08:37Z",
